animal.description:
Spunky and sweet. Fun loving and cuddly. Playful and friendly. Loves her people, loves her doggie friends and loves her kitties as well. Edith (Edie) is the perfect family pet and companion. She's highly trainable and picks up new commands and routines quickly. Edie is housetrained but is still learning to signal when she needs to go out. She absolutely loves to play and a home with a yard where she can get the zoomies or enjoy a good game of fetch would be ideal for Edie. She's crate trained and although she is a full-on puppy, she can settle down after working off some of her energy. Edie will need to work on manners such as not being mouthy or jumping up but she has already shown signs of being able to break these puppy habits quickly and she is working on basic commands such as sit and wait. Edie has a big, loveable personality and will definitely bring joy to any home. 





PLEASE NOTE:  While this Lab may not be available for adoption by the time you complete the adoption process, other great Labs are always finding their way into our Rescue. 

For more information on this Lab, please contact INFO@BROOKLINELABRESCUE.ORG.  

If you are interested in adopting this Lab or any other Lab from our Rescue, please visit our Web site, www.brooklinelabrescue.org, for more information on our adoption process. If you need additional information about the adoption process or whether you are in our coverage area, please send an e-mail to our Rescue at info@brooklinelabrescue.org

Even if you are not ready to adopt, you can still help us help our Labs!

Brookline Labrador Retriever Rescue is a 501(c)3 non-profit volunteer organization funded entirely by donations. Donations are always needed to help with veterinary costs, transportation, and supplies for our dogs. For information on donating to BLRR please click here. Donations are accepted via PayPal or you can mail a check to: Brookline Labrador Retriever Rescue, P.O. Box 638, Warrington, PA 18976-0638

animal.description:
Meet Remo! This darling 7 lbs little guy was rescued from the streets of TJ and is now looking for a forever home. He is working on his potty skills and if very friendly with other dogs.

Remo is approx 2 yrs old


PLEASE NOTE: Breed mix info is the best guess of ScratchMyBelly and our vets. There is no way to know for certain what any dog's breed mix is without a DNA test, so we have no way to know whether or not this dog is "hypoallergenic". Since he/she is a mixed breed, and could have as many as 4-5 breeds in his/her mix, it is safest to assume this dog is NOT hypoallergenic.
Homes with doggie doors will not be approved, sorry we are seeing a lot of problems with unsupervised animals and wild life.

We require a Home Check to set you & our Dog up for a successful transition into his/her furever home. This is only about the safety of the dog & in no way a judgement of you or your home. Our contract states that should you not want our Dog for ANY reason we will happily take our Dog back into our Rescue.

*WE NEED AN ADOPTION APPLICATION TO START THE PROCESS*

1. Submit Application
Go to our website www.scratchmybelly.org/forms. Your application is not a guarantee of placement, our process is not first come, first serve and we have the right to refuse the application. If you “rent” please make sure you check with your Landlord you can have a pet prior to submitting your application, many landlords have weight and/or breed restrictions.

2. Interview
We endeavor to make sure we are matching you with the right dog so a phone interview helps to insure we are all on the same page.

3. Meet the Pet
We can Meet n Greet at Home Check or you meet the foster. Every situation is different. We try to accommodate each on a personal level.

4. Home Check
We check for safety for the dog. We know our dogs well & can spot a potential problem quickly. We also call this a meet n greet.

5. Sign Adoption Contract
Contracts are signed the day of adoption, we accept PayPal to the Rescue Group & the Dog goes to his new home.

Due to the hundreds of inquires we cannot guarantee anything. ALL THE APPLICATIONS ARE SENT TO THE FOSTER FOR REVIEW.   IF THE FOSTER CHOOSES YOUR HOME FOR ONE OF OUR DOGS, SHE WILL "CALL YOU" WITHIN FIVE DAYS OF RECEIVING YOUR APPLICATION.   OTHERWISE, YOU WILL NOT HEAR FROM THE FOSTER.

It does not help us if you are sending us multiple emails, texts and calls. 
We are a volunteer based rescue organization.

animal.description: Everyone loves a sweet sensitive guy and that's exactly what Rocky is! He is 4 years and currently weighs in at a hefty 75 pounds, which means, no matter how much he gives you that sad face, he's going to need to trim off a few pounds. Rocky will most likely need a little time to settle in as he can be a bit worried in new situations. Once comfortable, he's happy to sit on your lap or ask you to shake hands. He may be able to live with another dog, but he can be particular about who he likes to be friends with, a mellow dog would be the best fit for this good boy. And of course this means that Rocky will not be a dog park kind of guy nor will he want to meet every dog he may see. With a slow introduction, Rocky can have a cat friend in his new home and as an extra bonus, he has a good history around chickens. He says older kids are fine as long as they give him some space while he settles in. If you think Rocky might be for you, please start by filling out the form that is provided in the link below. mspca.org/nevinsadoptioninquiry

animal.description: Simone, our wild child! And we say that with lots of love in our heart! She is aaaalllll the things - young, energetic, frustrated, adorable, silly. The shelter is such a tough environment for Simone... she sits in her kennel all day watching people and other dogs go by and her frustration grows and grows. We need to get this little nugget into a foster home stat! Simone is such a different pup when she is away from her kennel and other dogs. She's wiggly, affectionate, trying to get as close to her person as possible. Simone gives the sweetest kisses, and offers up her precious little belly to get rubbed... of course, we oblige! At just over a year old, Simone is still pretty much a puppy, and puppies should not grow up in the shelter. We have no doubt that once Simone is in a home, and has time to catch up on her sleep and decompress, she will be such a lovely - and silly! - companion. She arrived as a stray so we don't have home notes on her but of course we are here to offer you all the support and tools you need to set her up for success! An ideal home for Simone is with an active person/family who will exercise both her body and her brain. A house with a fenced yard would be ideal. Simone is likely too much doggo for young kids. Let's get this youngin out of a kennel and into a home so she can flourish and learn and just get to be a dog! I weigh approximately 45 lbs. Click here to view my paperwork.
animal.name: SIMONE

MY NAME IS:  Hercules
POSTED TO PETFINDER DATE:  Jan 28, 2021
SIZE: 66 pounds
APPROXIMATE AGE: 2 years
SHELTER STAFF SAYS:  "How am I supposed to prove myself a hero if nobody will give me a chance?" Will you give Hercules a chance to be Your hero? Hercules is a big, strong boy who is learning how to use his power to be a hero, but he needs a guiding hand and a happy home to become the best! He will need a little work on leash, but will always try his hardest! Come meet Hercules today and you will find the best champion, the best protector, the best Hero you will ever know! “I will face the world, fearless, proud, and strong…I can go the distance.”

Due to Covid, we now work by appointment only and work on a first come basis.  If you are interested in making an appointment, please call the HCHS at 512-793-5463.  You can see all our available animals at HillCountryHumaneSociety.org.
All our adoptable dogs are treated for fleas, given DHPPV and Bordatella vaccines and are de-wormed.  
When you adopt one of our animals it will be micro chipped and registered at the time of adoption.  Also, if not already altered, you will receive a voucher to get your animal spay/neutered.
While we do our best to determine the breeds of our dogs, the majority are strays, and we have only general appearance, coat type, size, ear type, tail, tongue color and coat color to base breed on.  It is always possible when adopting a puppy that it will change dramatically to look like another breed.

She's spayed, microchipped and up to date on her shots. animal.description:
ADOPTION REQUIREMENTS
Fenced yard
Canine sibling

My name is Sarah, sometimes, sweet and often sassy, I am looking for a forever home. I am just maybe 6 months old; my foster brother said that my feet indicate I might be on the larger size. I think I will be a perfect what ever size I grow to. I will most likely be the size of a Boxer, for that is what I am, with some Mastiff and Heinz 57 mixed in. 
I eat in my crate, I have a slow eating bowl, I tend to gulp my food, and my foster mom tells me that is not good for me. I eat two times a day, if you leave food out, I will eat it.  I just can not help myself.  
I have a foster fur brother, he is a Mastiff, (we are not related,) we play inside and outside together. I have had no accidents in the house, and go out several times a day. I am used to being in my crate, I do require a treat to get in. 
I had a forever family, but they couldn’t keep me, they surrendered me to 4 the Love of K9’s. I had other dogs there that I played with, and a young child too. I don’t know if I like cats or not, haven’t been around one, I don’t think. 
I need bones, toys and kongs to chew on, I like to chew. Foster mom said something about I could possibly be cutting more teeth. Speaking of teeth, I play hard, I would do better with a family who are familiar with Bully breeds. My foster mom says, I need boundaries. A fur brother or two would be fun, they need to be about 60 pounds and like to wrestle. A fenced yard is a must too. 
I have been vetted and spayed, and am excited about a new adventure with my forever family. 
I don’t know if I like to walk on a leash, foster mom and I haven’t done this. I suspect I will like walking and seeing the sites. 

If you would like to meet Sarah send us an email to theloveofk9s@yahoo.com and we will get back with you as quick as we can.

Adoption donation pays for all vetting...spay, a heart worm test, all vaccinations, deworming, flea prevention, a microchip and a wellness exam.

animal.description:
Meet Butters! He is approx 1-2 yrs old and about 6-7 lbs, he was rescued from the streets of TJ. He is neutered, vaccinated, microchipped and dewormed. He is doing really good at potty training and he is already a professional cuddler.

PLEASE NOTE: Breed mix info is the best guess of ScratchMyBelly and our vets. There is no way to know for certain what any dog's breed mix is without a DNA test, so we have no way to know whether or not this dog is "hypoallergenic". Since he/she is a mixed breed, and could have as many as 4-5 breeds in his/her mix, it is safest to assume this dog is NOT hypoallergenic.


Homes with doggie doors will not be approved, sorry we are seeing a lot of problems with unsupervised animals and wild life.

We require a Home Check to set you & our Dog up for a successful transition into his/her furever home. This is only about the safety of the dog & in no way a judgement of you or your home. Our contract states that should you not want our Dog for ANY reason we will happily take our Dog back into our Rescue.

*WE NEED AN ADOPTION APPLICATION TO START THE PROCESS*

1. Submit Application
Go to our website www.scratchmybelly.org/forms. Your application is not a guarantee of placement, our process is not first come, first serve and we have the right to refuse the application. If you “rent” please make sure you check with your Landlord you can have a pet prior to submitting your application, many landlords have weight and/or breed restrictions.

2. Interview
We endeavor to make sure we are matching you with the right dog so a phone interview helps to insure we are all on the same page.

3. Meet the Pet
We can Meet n Greet at Home Check or you meet the foster. Every situation is different. We try to accommodate each on a personal level.

4. Home Check
We check for safety for the dog. We know our dogs well & can spot a potential problem quickly. We also call this a meet n greet.

5. Sign Adoption Contract
Contracts are signed the day of adoption, we accept PayPal to the Rescue Group & the Dog goes to his new home.

Due to the hundreds of inquires we cannot guarantee anything. ALL THE APPLICATIONS ARE SENT TO THE FOSTER FOR REVIEW.   IF THE FOSTER CHOOSES YOUR HOME FOR A PUPPY, SHE WILL "CALL YOU" WITHIN FIVE DAYS OF RECEIVING YOUR APPLICATION.   OTHERWISE, YOU WILL NOT HEAR FROM THE FOSTER.

It does not help us if you are sending us multiple emails, texts and calls. 
We are a volunteer based rescue organization.

Required: Sturdy physical fenced yard as this boy loves to run and play but will climb a 4 ft chain link fence. A buddy for him to play with would be great.

Sunny is (best guess) a lab mix who is 10 mths old and around 45 lbs. He has ears that are designed to make you smile every time you see him. 
Sunny is one big happy kid! He is full of personality and will 'talk' to the foster. He also is a shadow to her if allowed and enjoys cuddles and she says shows nothing but love and devotion to her. He loves to play with the other dogs and toys. He especially loves playing fetch with a ball. He is learning to play less rough with kitties, so probably no cats in his forever home. He bonds quickly and is completely house-trained. He uses the dog door easily and loves his time outside, especially if one of his buddies is out there, too. He enjoys treats and learns new things pretty quickly.  He needs an active home and no toddlers/young kids as he is higher energy. He will climb a 4 ft chain link fence so more solid or higher fencing is needed. If you would like to meet this adorable pup an application must be filled out https://www.cognitoforms.com/New2URescues/AdoptionApplication

You can learn more about our rescue and process at www.new2urescue.org or find us on facebook at https://new2urescue.org/adoption/adoption-application/ must be filled out to meet one of our dogs.  You must be 25 yrs of age or older to adopt through us. We are in the Rochester NY area and adopt dogs out to area residents.



https://www.cognitoforms.com/New2URescues/AdoptionApplication
An application must be filled out to meet any of our dogs, to apply go to 
http://new2urescue.org/adoption/adoption-application/ so foster can contact you. We do not have a shelter, dogs are in foster homes.

All animals are kept in foster homes so there is no shelter for you to visit animal. Please go to https://new2urescue.org/adoption/adoption-application/ if you would like to meet the foster animal or learn more.

All our dogs have been spayed/neutered; treated for worms; heartworm tested (if age appropriate -7 mths or older); treated for fleas/ticks; microchip; and examined by veterinarian and given age appropriate vaccinations. We take every effort to ensure the health of the animal and you will receive a copy of all vet work performed.

You can find us on Face Book at https://www.facebook.com/New2Urescue and our main website at https://www.new2urescue.org

New 2 U Rescue is registered as a New York State Shelter / Rescue. Our Registration No.: is RR033 and we are a Registered Non Profit with a 501c3. We help dogs in need in the Greater Rochester, NY area by taking them in, providing any needed vet care and helping them find a forever home.

animal.description:
Sophie and Santanna are a bonded pair of pom mixes! They are adorable. However, their owner declined and was no longer able to care for them. They are the sweetest pair.  Sophie is a little less energetic than her younger sibling, so they would prefer a quieter home.

Sophie is 9yo, black and white female pom mix. When she first came into foster, she could not walk very well, but as she has been slowly introduced to more exercise, her joints have improved! She now can take short walks and is able to walk across hardwood floors. The vet checked her out and said she needs gentle exercise to keep her joints strengthened. She's in great health overall!  She a sweet, loving, calm girl. Rarely barks.

Santanna is a 7yo male tan pom mix. He is playful and fun with a medium energy level. He is more outgoing than Sophie. The vet says he's in great shape! He's sweet and spunky, and his foster notes he rarely barks.

The adoption donation amount is for both Sophie and Santanna together. Please contact us if you would like to welcome this adorable pair into your home.

** IMPORTANT NOTICE **
Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, dog adoptions are currently being done by appointment only. Contact 311 to schedule an appointment. Thank you!

______________________________

Come Meet Our Adoptable Dogs...
Winnipeg Animal Services Agency
1057 Logan Avenue
Winnipeg, Manitoba, Canada
R3E 3N8

Phone: 311 - outside Winnipeg dial 1-877-311-4974 

Email: animalservicesagency@winnipeg.ca

Our hours for adoption are Monday to Friday from 11:00 am - 5:30 pm
Saturday & Sunday from 12:00 pm - 4:30pm.
Animal Services is closed on statutory holidays.

BACKGROUND
Almost all the dogs at Animal Services are picked up as strays running loose on the streets of Winnipeg and therefore they come to us with no known history. For this reason, we are not sure how they will interact with other dogs, cats or how they are with children. We would suggest that if you have younger children you bring them down with you to meet the dogs. We also have an outdoor play area where we can do introductions with any other dogs that live in the home.

All locally adopted dogs come with a 7 day home trial. If you return the dog within this time period, you will be refunded your adoption fee less the non-refundable deposit.

Please feel free to meet all the dogs and puppies outside of their kennels, just let the kennel attendants know that you would like a meet and greet with the dog outside of his pen. The dogs are much more relaxed when outside of their kennels. They would love to meet you!

animal.description:
Ebony is a young and small pit/lab x - about 45-50 lbs. Looks like she recently had puppies. Good Samaritan rescued her - no sign of the puppies. She has a nice disposition and is available for meet/greet only at this time. She will need booster vaccines and her spay surgery before leaving B&B. In the meanwhile, email your application to get an appointment to see her. Plan to bring the entire family and any other dog/s in the home.

Are you my furrever family?

For further info on the adoption process, please visit our home page and check out the "Adopt a Dog" section, which has thorough instructions. All our dogs are spayed/neutered, microchipped, and

fully vaccinated before adoption; they have been wormed, bathed, socialized, walked daily and much loved; each adoptee leaves with a leash, collar, and all medical records.

Our prices are higher than the shelters' because we nurse the dogs through their illnesses and get them needed surgeries and dentals. We also spend time socializing. Furthermore, unlike shelters, rescues do not get financial aid from the government and must rely on donations, grants, and adoption fees. Our fees for adults start at $150 and go up to $750. The higher end is for our most in demand dogs, such as young beagles and other purebred dogs. The lower end is for dogs who have been here a while. For puppies, we may go beyond this and charge $1000. The good news is that, because rescues fall under the "charity" category, the fees for our dogs are officially donations and are therefore tax deductible. You can think of it as donating to a worthy cause and getting a dog in return!

Sponsor Me

Beagles & Buddies must find ways to raise money so we can continue saving dogs. Your tax-deductible donation keeps our rescue kennel operating!

animal.description:
Allison, or Allie, is a very sweet, quiet little girl - 8-10 yrs old and 9-10 lbs. Came from a home - her family's health causes her to find another family. Poor eyesight, but she loves her walks- she'll even go on a walk when it's cold and windy! She is spending her time in our office with a few other small dogs - relaxing on a big pillow. She is taking proin to help her "hold her water" - might need to put a little doggie diaper on her. But maybe not - could be that the deteriorating health of her people was upsetting to her. She is usually good about where she does her business, as long as you pay attention to when she needs outside.

According to the shelter she originally came from, she would be 7 and a half; but the family that gave her up thinks she must be older, up to 10, because of her eyesight and low energy level. Her teeth are bad and we plan on giving her a dental. She has trouble eating hard kibble.

animal.description:
Hi, I'm Athena!

Do you like other dogs? I may do best as the only dog in the home. I can be selective with some dogs. I may be able to have a canine friend outside of my home. I do well with male dogs and I am selective with female dogs. 

What do you think about cats? I have an unknown history with cats.

So how do you feel about kids? I would do best with older kids. I can be protective over my food. So I will need kids old enough to know to leave me alone while I eat.

What's your energy level like? I have a medium to high energy level.

What is it that staff and volunteers love about you? I am a sweet girl who enjoys yard time! I would prefer a home where my owner is home most of the time! 

Is there anything else we should know about you? I am 5 years old and I weigh between 60-65 pounds. I do have a behavior waiver the staff will discuss with you.

I came into the shelter as a transfer and the above information is all recommendations based on my previous history and the behavior seen at the shelter. Expect to learn more about me after adoption.
It is unknown how this animal will do in their new home as all animals can be different with each person. It is important to take this into consideration when thinking about adopting and making sure you are prepared to work with any potential medical or behavior issues that occur after adoption.

My adoption fee includes my spay/neuter, current vaccinations, permanent microchip identification, certificate for a free veterinary exam, post-adoption support and more!

Thank you for taking the time to learn a little about me! If you think we would be a good match call and ask about me! I'm looking for my forever home and it could be with you!

ADOPTION INFORMATION: If you live in the city of Eugene or in Lane County you will be purchasing a dog license in addition to the adoption fee. You will get to choose between a one year, two year, or three year license. 
This pet is located at Greenhill Humane Society. 88530 Greenhill Road Eugene, OR 97402 (541) 689-1503. See all of the pets at this shelter by visiting www.green-hill.org.

animal.description:
Soup is up for adoption!

Age: 10 months
Gender: Male
Weight: 38lbs
Breed: GSD Mix
Dog Friendly: Yes
Cat Friendly: Yes
Potty Trained: Yes
Neutered: Yes
Microchipped: Yes
Heartworm: Negative 
Vaccinated: Yes
Location: Soup is being fostered in Elburn, IL. No out of state applicants, please. 

Crate Trained: Work in progress. He is very unhappy in the crate but if he’s got a dog friend near him, for comfort, he does well. 

Kids: No kids. Soup is child friendly but we’ve witnessed some food resource guarding. We want to ensure a long term home so we think no young children is best. 

Soup is a super sweet boy that is still learning the ropes. He and his buddy Malcolm have been inseparable since they’ve gone into their foster home together. We think Soup would benefit from another dog. 

Soup definitely has German Shepherd in him so he’s got one of those personalities. He can be quite noisy at times. We’d like Soup to go to a GSD experienced home who understands their traits. Soup really needs the security of living with another dog. 

He’s an overall really nice boy that should be a great addition to a family of GSD lovers. 

If you’re interested in meeting Soup, please fill out an application at animalheartline.org and a volunteer will contact you.

Nova has been in the program for 4 weeks now and has 4 more weeks to go. He is a fun, playful pup who enjoys people and other dogs. Her ideal new home will have plenty of room for her to run and lots of activities to keep her busy. She is jealous of other dogs getting attention so a home with a limited number of existing dogs is required. She will growl and push the other dog out of the way.

12/28/20--Nova is currently housed and enrolled in the Puppies for Parole Program at the Boonville Correction Center where (s)he will stay for 8 weeks of basic obedience training. (S)He will learn commands such as “sit”, “stay”, “heel”, “come”, etc. (S)He will learn crate and house training. Nova will be available for adoption while (s) he is in the Program, but will not be released to his/her new adopting family until the end of the 8 weeks when (s)he graduates. The adoption fee for a Puppies for Parole dog is $100. For questions regarding adoptions, call the Marshall Animal Shelter at (660)831-0420

Nova was originally found by a citizen at an abandoned gas station along a busy highway. They brought her back to their house where they unsuccessfully attempted to find her owner. They fostered her until the shelter had room to take her or find rescue placement for her. She was brought to the shelter after an altercation with one of the existing dogs in the home over a bone. She happily interacted with the families grandbaby who has Downs Syndrome. He's actually the one who named her! They report that she likes to go on walks and car rides.

Dogs are required to have a supervised visit with staff prior to adoption, as well as children. animal.description:
Champagne / Male / 10 Months / 24 lbs / Street Mix / Brampton

Meet Champagne! Champagne and all his siblings were brought to a spay and neuter campaign in Puebla City, Mexico. Their owners later called to say they would not be coming back for them. The puppies had already overcome a lot, so the selfless volunteers decided to give them a second chance. They were taken to the loving care of our partner shelter where they were prepared to fly to Canada. When they were ready, they were flown here in search of forever homes!

Champagne is the ultimate cuddle buddy and just wants to be close to his people. He loves tennis balls and cat toys that chirp! He is described as quiet, shy, affectionate, snuggly and social. He is always interested in what his people are doing and will follow his family from room to room. His ideal family would be home more often than not and have a confident doggy pal to show him the ropes!

With his family Champagne is a velcro dog. With new people he is shy but warms up quickly. He prefers if he is awarded the opportunity to come around on his own. He would be good with children, as long as the adults advocate for his space as needed. Paying close attention to his body language will be important for his comfort and success with all people.

Champagne has some mild separation anxiety and will cry when his humans leave. Even though he prefers to be with his people - he will settle in his crate after a few minutes. He is a very good boy and is becoming more confident every day being alone. Champagne is still learning house manners and will counter surf if given the chance!

On leash he is naturally a good boy. He will walk calmly and closely next to his people. He is still very much a puppy and will need ongoing support with commands and obedience skills. He knows sit, stay, lie down and is working on his recall. He is medium energy and will need at least two walks a day plus additional time to use the washroom. Granted he has received adequate opportunities outside, he is fully potty trained.

Champagne would do best in a detached house, with a fully fenced backyard. He would appreciate a safe and secured place to run and play with his canine siblings. He is easily startled by loud noises so he should always be supervised outdoors, and leashed if the space in not secured. The city would likely be overwhelming for Champagne, so he would prefer to be in the suburbs or quiet country. Champagne loves other dogs and cats!

If you’re interested in adopting Champagne please apply at https://www.fetchandreleash.ca/adoption-info#adoption-form

Champagne’s adoption fee is $800. To learn more about our adoption fees and the adoption process, please visit our FAQs at https://www.fetchandreleash.ca/about-us#about-faqs.

animal.description:
Boris / Male / 2 Years / 65 lbs / Catahoula Leopard Dog / Toronto

Meet Boris! Boris comes to us all the way from Hohenwald, Tennesee! This handsome and gentle giant is the ultimate cuddle buddy. His tail is always wagging and he is happiest when near his people. Wherever his person goes - he is sure to be close behind and curious about what they’re doing. He is described as shy, sweet, happy, friendly, calm, curious and affectionate. He loves playing with other dogs, chewing his bones, and exploring the outside. He would make the ultimate companion for an active family who shares his love of adventure!

Boris is the ultimate gentleman and never jumps up on anyone. He is very excited when his family comes home but is always calm and respectful. With new people he will go in for a sniff, and generally warms up very quickly. Based on his nature, he would make an incredible dog to grow up with respectful children of all ages.

Boris is currently getting 4 long walks a day. He is a working breed so he will need structured walks throughout the day to ensure he is successful. As long as he’s had enough exercise, he is extremely well mannered in the home. Boris is also fully potty trained!

When left alone Boris is crated and settles right away. Occasionally he whines a little at bedtime, but even then only takes a few minutes to settle completely. Once is comfortable he will sleep through the night without issue.

On leash Boris is a puller. He is a powerful dog so he should never be walked by children, only strong handlers. His leash etiquette should be a primary focus for his training moving forward. He is quite skittish outside and will jump or startle easily to loud noises. He will also need support with basic obedience and commands.

Boris’s ideal home would be a detached house, with a fully fenced backyard. He is used to wide open spaces to run and play, so would do best with a safely secured place to enjoy the outdoors. He could potentially adapt to an apartment if his family is committed to lots of exercise and mental stimulation throughout the day. Boris is only looking for homes outside of the city, where he can really start to thrive. Boris would do best with at least one other playful dog in the home, but has not been tested with cats.

If you’re interested in adopting Boris please apply at https://www.fetchandreleash.ca/adoption-info#adoption-form

Boris’s adoption fee is $700. To learn more about our adoption fees and the adoption process, please visit our FAQs at https://www.fetchandreleash.ca/about-us#about-faqs.

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
Name: Godiva

DOB: 2016

Weight: 80

Adoption Fee: $125

Are you looking for an exercise buddy? Then keep scrolling - this is not your dog! Clementine is a couch potato better suited to binge watching Netflix during a pandemic. She is an adult (~4 year old) Coonhound mix who loves laying on the couch, chewing on bones in the yard and taking short walks through the neighborhood. She loves other dogs but we don't know about cats or small pets. She is 100% hound and needs people who can be strong leaders and will understand her breed. She has shown some possessive behavior with toys but is easily redirected. Car rides are a big hit and she likes being tucked in with a blanket at bedtime. Clementine is a dog built for comfort, not speed. Spayed, microchipped and housebroken. Ready for your couch!

Due to Godiva/Clementines size and resource guarding of toys we are asking for an adoptive family with large dog experience and kids over the age of 16.

In the meantime if you have questions or are interested in me, please fill out an adoption application at www.ruffstartrescue.org.

An adoption application is the best way to show your interest in an animal. Please check out our website, www.ruffstartrescue.org for more details and additional pictures on any of our animals! All Ruff Start dogs and cats are spayed/neutered, up to date on age appropriate vaccines, microchipped, dewormed, and on monthly flea/tick and heartworm prevention (dogs) as well as heartworm tested (dogs). Ruff Start Rescue is a foster based rescue. Animals are located in homes throughout Minnesota. We do not have a facility where animals are kept. Ruff Start Rescue Adoption Policies: http://www.ruffstartrescue.org/info/display?PageID=11744

If you're looking for a fun, energetic puppy that can run like the wind Promethius is the dog for you!! Promethius was given up by his owner due to being too energetic. Evidently, he was kept in his kennel for 20+ hours a day so learned to use the bathroom in there. Luckily, he's learning house training at the BCC. He has a bad habit of jumping on people, but is also learning good manners at the training program.
Promethius has been in the program for 4 weeks now and has 4 more weeks to go. He is a fun, playful pup who enjoys people and other dogs. His ideal new home will have plenty of room for him to run and lots of activities to keep him busy.
12/28/20--Promethius is currently housed and enrolled in the Puppies for Parole Program at the Boonville Correction Center where (s)he will stay for 8 weeks of basic obedience training. (S)He will learn commands such as “sit”, “stay”, “heel”, “come”, etc. (S)He will learn crate and house training. Promethius will be available for adoption while (s) he is in the Program, but will not be released to his/her new adopting family until the end of the 8 weeks when (s)he graduates. The adoption fee for a Puppies for Parole dog is $100. For questions regarding adoptions, call the Marshall Animal Shelter at (660)831-0420

Thanks for stopping by, were you stunned by my glamour shot?! My name is Archer and I'm looking for a home of my own. As you may have noticed, I'm a petite fella, but don't let that fool you, I have lots of energy to share with you! I enjoy going on walks and chasing after scents or wild critters that come by, which is why I learned to walk on a harness and sturdy leash. When I'm hanging out at home, I like to play with plush toys, chew on appropriate bones and practice some self-care by taking naps in my crate.

Though I've gained several skills while at the BRC*, I will do best in a structured home where my people can help me continue to become comfortable in the world. I gain a lot of confidence from being with other dogs, so I am looking for a home with another dog, preferably a social and confident one. Once I'm comfortable with you I will keep you entertained with my silly antics - I can't wait!

*Archer is a recent graduate of the ASPCA's Behavioral Rehabilitation Center (BRC) in Weaverville, NC. The BRC is the first and only facility of its kind dedicated to the study and rehabilitation of extremely fearful dogs. animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
Name: Garnet

DOB: 1/20/2018

Weight: 14

Adoption Fee: 375

Info from my foster Parent below!!

He is working on potty training. He will have accidents when in his crate and inside still. Also he does not like the snow. I'm not sure he understands the concept of going for walks because he often stops, looks confused, gets EASILY distracted if anyone walks by. He can only walk in the cold for so long until he gives up. His little feetsies get cold.. I doubt he's encountered much snow where he came from. It's going to take a lot of patience and work to get the walks down and learn they're for going potty.

Not too good in the crate as far as being left alone, especially during bed time or when we are away at work. I believe he may have separation anxiety because when I leave for work he will bark loudly. So no shared wall living situations. He needs lots of attention and I don't think he should be left alone for very long. I think he would do best with someone who works from home or a few adults who have staggering shifts so that as soon as one leaves him alone, the next one will be along shortly for the remainder of the time until the primary comes home. Something like that.

He's okay with my cat. Only snapped at him once I wasn't looking at the time it happened but I believe it was in defense of a chewable bone. Aside from that, the resident cat and Garnet have been tolerating each other nicely. Both curious. I even got them to lay within a foot from each other for nap time . He gets jealous if I pay attention to the cat so I'll try to split the affection equally. He will lay in his bed and act like he doesn't notice, but is staring the entire time with the side eye of me paying attention to another animal. How dare I! Haha

Loves his belly rubs and starting to have fun with all the new toys and treats I bought for him. He's really warming up to me. I can't say how he is around kids as I haven't really been around any. And as for dogs, same thing, but when going for walks, if he sees another one, he's curious, but hasn't barked or sniffed or tried to attack another one, so he seems to be okay with the fact that other dogs exist. :)

Since Garnet is heartworm positive. He will need to be treated at a clinic in St. Cloud.

Heartworm treatment consists of 3 injections. The first injection will be in roughly 30 days after coming into rescue. The the 2nd and 3rd injections happen 30 days after that. When a dog is going through heartworm treatment, they should be on "restrictions", meaning a lot of lap time, crate time and always on a leash. Heartworm disease is NOT contagious, it is transported via mosquitos.

Here is a great article explaining what heartworm is and how it's treated: https://www.heartwormsociety.org/pet-owner-resources/heartworm-basics

An adoption application is the best way to show your interest in an animal.

All Ruff Start dogs and cats are spayed/neutered, up to date on age appropriate vaccines, microchipped, dewormed, and on monthly flea/tick and heartworm prevention (dogs) as well as heartworm tested (dogs).

Ruff Start Rescue is a foster based rescue. Animals are located in homes throughout Minnesota. We do not have a facility where animals are kept.

Ruff Start Rescue Adoption Policies: http://www.ruffstartrescue.org/info/display?PageID=11744

animal.description:
Poor Leroy was a hunting dog who was abandoned by his owner. As you can see in the 2nd photo, he was severely underweight. He is a 7-8 year old Hound mix. He is a sweet boy in spite of the neglect he has suffered. He's friendly with people & dogs, loves to play and is eager to please you. Won't you give him a chance?

From his foster mom-Poor Leroy was found wondering around a remote area of thick woods in NC. He was flea infested, starving and near death. Luckily, he was found and taken to one of our partner rescuers who took him to a vet and nursed him back to health then contacted us. As a result of parasite infestation, Leroy was anemic and developed a heart murmur. Once in NJ Leroy was evaluated by a Veterinary Cardiologist who administrated a echocardiogram and diagnosed the murmur as a result of the anemia. Follow up bloodwork is normal and Leroy got a clean bill of health!!! Leroy is easy, laid back and gets along with dogs, large and small as well as cats. He seeks his human's attention and eager to please. He is playful and well behaved in doors, no crate needed. He is housebroken and has zero food aggression. Leroy is good on a leash and loves car rides. He has interacted with younger children and did well. Leroy would be a great first time dog owner or second dog since he is so easy going.

If you are interested in adopting Leroy, please visit www.ehrdogs.org and ask for him by name, LEROY GIO!

Welcome to the Wonderful World of Rescue Dachshunds. Look around and read their bios. Find a few whose personality seems to fit well. Consider one of our Well Seasoned Seniors who are truly wonderful and have so much to offer. Need help finding the best fit? We'll help with that too. Please fill out an application and let's get you all matched up with a loving new "furever' companion and friend. You'll find the application on the "Available Dogs" page.

NOTE:

Adoptions to Central/South Texas residents only

Standard Adoption Fee Adult Dog: $250 ea. Puppy Adoption Fee: $300 ea. Reduced rates for Seniors dogs (10 and up). Reduced rates for pairs (when adopted together). All adoption fees are subject to sales tax per the State of Texas. DDRTX only adopts in Central/South Texas.

Email: ddrtxinfo@gmail.com Primary Website: www.DDRTX.org
Pioneer Puppy #3 - Teagan is the momma

Marco Polo is part of the pioneer pups born in our rescue. He and another one of the puppies tried a home but it didn't work out due to no fault of their own. Marco is almost 6 months old. This sweet puppy is so gentle and loving. He loves to cuddle, play fetch with a ball and go for walks. His favorite think in the world is belly rubs. He gets along with other dogs and children too! He is already crate trained and he is quickly on his way to being completely housebroken.

Love dachshunds and not ready to adopt or circumstances won't permit having a dog? How about being a sponsor or making a donation. Every one of our dachshunds receives excellent medical care along with day to day food, love and housing. Being non-profit, we rely on generous individuals like yourselves to help save these fur babies. You can do this specifically for one dog with the sponsor button on their webpage or a general donation on our "How To Help" page. Easy and quick through Pay Pal or your debit/credit card. You generosity is sincerely appreciated by all and is tax deductable. Need other ideas? You'll find tons of them on the How to Help tab. All contributions are tax deductable.

Diamond Dachshund Rescue of Texas is a non-profit 501(c)(3) volunteer organization with focus on rescue and adoption of pure breed Dachshunds. All dogs are fully vetted and housed on private property. Meetings are scheduled upon adoption approval. Thank you for your continued support to the rescue and shelter communities!
Opt to Adopt!

animal.description: Oreo #7621 is a 10-year-old male Pomeranian mix. He is friendly, sweet and calm. He has a low energy level and likes to chill. His foster mom says he is perfect! Oreo is good with other dogs, cats  and kids. He is both crate and house trained. He responds to the command: sit. He walks well on a leash. He is not very interested in treats. Oreo is picky about the dry food he eats. He prefers canned food. He loves to be held and carried around. He does have arthritis and will need to be on joint supplements. He just had a dental and has a shiny new smile.  He weighs 15 pounds and is full grown. This pup is microchipped. We believe you can always teach an ‘old’ dog new tricks, so we highly recommend continued obedience training for this smart pup; it stimulates the dog's mind and establishes a good dog/adopter relationship. This pup, like all pups, should be on heartworm preventative; an ounce of prevention is worth a pound of cure. If you are interested in adopting this dog, and are already approved to adopt through our organization, please contact dogs@lastchanceanimalrescue.org with the pup’s name and ID number in the subject line. OTHERWISE, please submit an adoption application online: http://www.lastchanceanimalrescue.org/adoptus.html E-mail dogs@lastchanceanimalrescue.org with questions. Stay tuned to our Facebook page for updates: www.facebook.com/LCARMD #adoptlove #PicMe #petsmartcharities

animal.description: A398558 Merlin Lab Mix 5 months Old Neutered Male Meet Merlin! This young, handsome guy is looking for a family who loves to train! Merlin is a typical rambunctious puppy who loves to use his brain...and his mouth! He would do best in a home where his family could manage his enviornment and spend lots of helping him learn manners. Merlin is already a big boy at 5 months old and still has growing to do, so we want to make sure he grows into a well behaved boy. Merlin likes other dogs, but play rough and can be a bit of a bully. He could potentially live with another dog who was very tolerant and had good manners to help teach Merlin the right way! If you are looking for a fun buddy to do lots of training with Merlin might just be your guy!

animal.description:
COSMO
Chihuahua Mix
(DOB: 06/01/19)

Cosmo is a sweet and playful little bundle of joy who needs your patience and love. He came from a tough situation, so he is a little more timid than most dogs.  However, within an hour of knowing you he warms right up. Then he is a very playful and silly pup.

Cosmo is flourishing in his foster home where he loves to play with the smaller dogs and does well with the cat.  He is crate-trained, although he doesn't like it during the day.  At night he is cozy in the crate or his foster parent’s bed, where he loves to put himself under the covers.

Cosmo does well on walks, although loud noises and cars do make him cower a bit.  He also gets car sick, but that might change as he grows. 

* We do not recommend him for small children as he is still a little skittish.

Cosmo still has more training and relaxing to go, but he is doing so well. He needs a forever home that can understand his fears and help him gain his confidence, which we are seeing in him already. 

This dog is currently being fostered as part of Diamonds in the Ruff Canine Rescue. An application is required, along with a home visit and small adoption fee.  Applicants must be at least 21 years of age. **FENCED IN YARD REQUIRED**

Please visit us on our Facebook page for additional photos, give us a like while you're there! 
https://www.facebook.com/diamondsintheruffNC

All of our dogs are fostered in homes and are INDOOR dogs. We believe all dogs are family members and should be treated as valued members of the household. 

All applicants must be 25 years of age or older.

Please review our adoption guidelines for further information on adopting from Diamonds in the Ruff Canine Rescue before submitting an application. www.DITRnc.com.


.

animal.description:
Meet Ernesto!

Ernesto is a lovable one! We believe he is a Plott Hound/Staffy mix about 2-3 years old and about 35 lbs. He is an absolute sweetheart.He is dog friendly, people friendly, and kid friendly. I'm unsure how he is with cats since he was not cat tested. Ernesto loves to cuddle and he is curious as well. He is very submissive and has an amazing personality that anyone will fall in love with. He's also unique and special while having only 3 legs. He'll make someone truly happy and will be a wonderful companion to someone. He'd be great in a moderate-active home and he would love to go on brisk walks and hikes. Preferably a house without stairs would be nice for the little guy! He is excited to meet his furever family! He is being fostered in Moses Lake,WA until he finds his perfect home

He is up to date on vaccines according to age, has received proper deworming, and comes with additional dewormer if needed. This pet is microchipped, spayed/neutered, comes with 2-6 months of Heartworm preventative, and one month free trial of pet insurance if registered by adopter with insurance company. All animals receive a health certificate (stating that a licensed veterinarian saw the pet and deemed it healthy for travel, but is not a promise of perfect health.) Our transports are USDA certified and the cost of transport is included in adoption fee!

For any questions of inquires please directly contact violet@threelittlepittiesrescue.org

Application link: https://petstablished.com/adoption_form/30285/generic

**Application is required to be considered*

animal.description:
Don’t “horse” around too long and miss your chance at adopting your bestie! My name is Rein! I am a cute, 2 year old, 20lb., Hound mix. I am a laidback, sweet girl ready to find my forever family. I get a little excited when you first come home but settle down rather quickly. I have mastered house and crate training! I am a doll on the leash and would do well in an apartment. I get along great with cats and other dogs too. Don’t “horse” around and miss out on your forever bestie! Apply today! 


My adoption fee is $150 and includes my spay/neuter, vaccinations, wellness exam, heartworm test, and microchip! If you're interested in meeting/adopting me, please visit www.rescueonespringfield.com/our-adoption-process/adoption-application/ and fill out the form! We do adopt out of state with vet references and video home check. *Adopter is responsible for coming to get the dog and returning the dog if the adoption does not work out* 

Don't forget to LIKE us on Facebook!-www.facebook.com/rescueonespringfield

*Remember, dogs are pack animals. Because of this, Rescue One does not adopt to outdoor-only homes. Pets are family and are not disposable.  Please make sure that you are 100% committed to a pet before considering adding one to your home.

Nashville adoption application: https://www.wagsandwalks.org/adoption-application-nashville

Meet Scooby!! This handsome guy is a 3-year-old Boxer/Pittie mix that weighs around 65 lbs. If you’ve been wishing for a real life Scooby Doo - he’s here!

This boy is super goofy and has a fun personality that is larger than life! Scooby is social, loves meeting new people, and is super affectionate. When Scooby came into our program, we quickly learned that he is a large dog with puppy tendencies who has little control of his limbs ?. We decided it’d be best to do a board and train with @fullcirclecanine to improve his manners and master his basics! In the week that he’s been there, he has made tremendous progress. He will thrive with an adopter who is dedicated to continuing his training and can provide him the structure he needs. Scooby will benefit from a home with a yard to explore and an adopter who lives an active lifestyle. He’s now ready to find his forever home, and be the Scooby Doo to your Shaggy!

animal.description:
Willie Nelson is an approximate 9 year old pure breed Pomeranian that is an owner surrender from southern Iowa. He came into foster care on July 30, 2020. He was in horrible condition from what we thought was severe neglect for an extended period of time. After getting him to the vet, immediately, it was determined after a thorough exam and testing, that Willie has an autoimmune disorder called Erythema multiforme. This condition triggers his immune system to attack his skin cells and destroy them. He lost all of his fur and several layers of skin over several months before we got his condition stabilized. He is on medication to stabilize his condition but it is something that can not be cured. We hope he will regrow the fur on his back, but only time will tell. Willie was also diagnosed with dry eyes and has ulcers on his eyes. He can see good enough that he can navigate in his surroundings, but he is not comfortable doing any stairs on his own for the most part. His close vision is the worst. He does require a medicated ointment for his eyes twice daily and artificial tears applied a few times a day as well. Willie is house trained but due to his bad eye sight he is carried outside to go potty and carried back in by his foster mom. He will not be able to go on leash walks but he does enjoy sniffing around the yard and laying in the shade when the weather is nice. Due to not knowing what triggered his disease, he is on a special veteranarian diet and will need to stay on that for the rest of his life as well. He will require baths with a special shampoo on occasion and ointment applied to his ears every few days to help remove the scaly thick skin that does not shed off normally. His condition can be painful so a gentle touch is required when touching and picking him up. He does well with dogs as long as they leave him alone. He would be best with other older dogs or no dogs in the home. He has no interaction with the cats in his foster home. Due to his condition and the pain he can experience some times, he needs a home with children 13 and above or no children. Willie is very affectionate and loves to be held and petted. He spends most of his time lounging on the couch on his 'special Prince pillow' as his foster mom affectionately calls his soft and cozy pillow. His resilience is amazing and the fact that he is such a loving, sweet, and happy boy is testament to just how special this boy is. The cost associated with Willie's continued care is about $100 per month right now but it could go up as he ages. His adopter will need to work closely with their veteranarian to keep Willie's conditions stable and be willing to put in the time to maintain his strict personal care every day.

Adoption fee is $150 (senior rate) which includes spay/neuter, age-appropriate vaccines/tests, and microchip.

If you would like to meet Willie Nelson, please complete an online application that can be found at: http://hopeanimalrescueofiowa.org/forms/196/dog-application

animal.description:
Meet Cora! 
Cora is the sweetest ball of energy you'll ever meet! She was scheduled to be euthanized in Clyde, TX but we just couldn't let that happen. I mean, look at that face! She is around 2 years old and weighs around 35-40 pounds. Cora loves to play with her foster dog brothers. She plays hard and naps harder. Cora isn't a huge fan of the crate but won't fight you to get in it. We are working on potty training but she has had very few accidents in the house, knows what "let's go outside" means, and is doing so well. Cora loves to snuggle with her human fosters and wants to be by one of their sides at all times. All in all, Cora would be perfect in any home but would prefer a family with an active lifestyle and a canine sibling for her to play with.

To set up a meet and greet or inquire about a dog, please first fill out an application at https://savinghoperescue.org/contact. It doesn't obligate you, but it is the first step. We don't get to all of the inquiries but respond to all applications. Thank you for choosing to rescue!

animal.description:
Hi, I'm Stella!

Do you like other dogs? I do not seem to enjoy the company of other dogs. I would likely do best as the only dog in the home. 

What do you think about cats? I have an unknown history with cats. 

So how do you feel about kids? I would do best with older kids that can give me my space when needed. 

What's your energy level like? I have a medium to high energy level.

What is it that staff and volunteers love about you? I am a super sweet girl who enjoys walks and attention!

Is there anything else we should know about you? I am 3 yrs old and I weigh between 55-60 pounds. I do have a medical release the staff will discuss with you.

I came into the shelter as a transfer and the above information is all recommendations based on my previous history and the behavior seen at the shelter. Expect to learn more about me after adoption.
It is unknown how this animal will do in their new home as all animals can be different with each person. It is important to take this into consideration when thinking about adopting and making sure you are prepared to work with any potential medical or behavior issues that occur after adoption.

My adoption fee includes my spay/neuter, current vaccinations, permanent microchip identification, certificate for a free veterinary exam, post-adoption support and more!

Thank you for taking the time to learn a little about me! If you think we would be a good match call and ask about me! I'm looking for my forever home and it could be with you!

ADOPTION INFORMATION: If you live in the city of Eugene or in Lane County you will be purchasing a dog license in addition to the adoption fee. You will get to choose between a one year, two year, or three year license. 
This pet is located at Greenhill Humane Society. 88530 Greenhill Road Eugene, OR 97402 (541) 689-1503. See all of the pets at this shelter by visiting www.green-hill.org.

animal.description:
To be considered for adopting a dog from Canine Lifeline, you must have an approved application must be on file. Please visit http://www.caninelifeline.org/adoption-process/ for more information about our adoption process and to submit an online application.

Sweet Nala is a 3-4 year-old Boxer/Mountain Cur mix female with perhaps a little Pittie in her family tree who has a very kind and gentle disposition. She found herself homeless at an overcrowded rural county dog shelter and after being in the shelter for several weeks, made the trip to Canine Lifeline so she could relax in a foster home while searching for a permanent new home. While we don't have any history on this lovely girl, she has been the perfect houseguest in her foster home since arriving here with us. Nala has enjoyed meeting new people and has gotten along well with every dog she's met since her arrival here. She has had several litters of pups in the past but her days as a mom are now over as Nala is spayed and ready to live her life as someone's pampered pup for a change. Nala was very stoic in front of the camera but she always greets her foster mom with a big smile and whole body wag. She walks quite well on the leash, knows the sit command, and takes treats very gently. Nala can get quite playful at times now that her hard days are behind her. She may jump up seeking attention from her human friends when she's excited but is very responsive to training. Nala has had excellent crate manners in her foster home and may be housetrained too although we can't guarantee it. She might enjoy having a canine buddy in her home but would likiely also be fine as the only dog in the home provided her family has plenty of time to shower her with lots of love and attention. We can't wait to see this sweetheart settle into her very own home. Nala weighs about 65 pounds and her adoption fee is $325. She's spayed, heartworm negative and on monthly preventative, up to date on vaccinations including bivalent canine influenza, wormed, on flea and tick preventative, and microchipped. As part of the adoption process, all adopters must commit to a two-week adjustment period to make sure it's a great match before the adoption is finalized. Please email info@caninelifeline.org if you're interested in Nala. An approved application is required before we schedule meets with any of our dogs. Please note that we don't place our dogs in homes with children under 7 years of age. We correspond via email so please check your junkmail or spam folder to make sure our reply hasn't landed in there. Please visit our website at www.caninelifeline.org to see more photos of Nala and to submit an online application if you live in Northeast OH.

animal.description:
**if you're interested in learning more about Abraham, please email wlr@gmx.us**

Four score and a few years ago, Honest Abe was born!!

Abraham is perfectly content to be scratched, petted and snuggled by both men and women. He knows how to indicate to the other dog when he needs a time out and will go into his crate for that. He sleeps quietly through the night and loves the smallest dog bed that is at his foster home (despite larger beds being available) and will curl himself up into a contented ball. He doesnt seem to know commands yet, so his Foster Family is working on 'sit' as a first step. He walks nicely on the leash when it's quiet out (loud noises scare him, but he recovers quickly), he does require dedicated leash training which we're working on. He's a hound and can be determined to stay on the scent, so someone who can help him learn leash etiquette would do great with him! Abraham is still learning the ins and outs of the house, like which is a toy and which is a shoe, and just which toy he wants to chew! He'd love someone that's patient with him and can bring him out of his shell more, he's warmed in his foster home and would love to melt your heart!

animal.description:
ADOPTION REQUIREMENTS
Fenced yard
Canine sibling

My name is Markie. I was found running the streets and no one ever came looking for me so I am in the market for a new home. I am about 4 years old and weigh in at 14lbs. I am a super fun little dude and like to be on the go but I am also a snuggle bug my foster mom says. I love going for walks and hanging out playing in the yard. I would do best with a dog sibling that likes to play also. I am fine with kids but probably a little older would be best. I am fine with cats but if they run I will chase them. They run because they want to play, right?? I am a little shy at first but that passes quickly. I am crate trained and still working on be housebroken. I came with a nasty infection that has since been cleared up but during the time I had it I couldn't hold it and now I have to be reminded where I am supposed to use the bathroom. 

If you would like to meet Markie send us an email to theloveofk9s@yahoo.com and we will get back to you as quick as we can.

Adoption donation pays for all vetting...neuter, a heart worm test, all vaccinations, deworming, flea prevention, a microchip and a wellness exam

Meet Niihau a 13 week old female Bloodhound Shepherd mix. This sweet girl has been rescued and is so excited to meet her furever family. Niihau, currently, lives in her foster home with two other dogs. She’s working hard on her potty training and sleeps in her crate at night. She also loves children of all ages. She has been spayed it is up-to-date on her shots. If you would like to meet this amazing girl please submit your application.

I will come with the works (Neutered/Spayed, up to date on everything, micro chipped, fecal, heartworm tested if age appropriate, heartworm, flea and tick preventative, one month insurance and free vet visit).  What more could a new family ask for?  COVID 19 restrictions:  If I have not been altered by adoption I will have to return to my vet for my procedure.

If you are interested in meeting and thinking about adoption, please visit our website http//www.wagginghearts.org and submit an adoption application. Include the name(s) of the animal(s) you are interested in the subject line of the email. Due to the high volume of applications we receive we are only able to process fully completed applications. We do not reply to inquiries. Since we are a foster based rescue we are unable to set up meet and greets until a completed application is on file and has been approved. 

Wagging Hearts is a 100% foster-based, non-profit rescue organization. 

Our mission is to rescue abandoned, neglected, and stray companion animals. Please visit http//www.wagginghearts.org if you would like to adopt and provide a forever home to one in need.

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Benny and I'm looking for an active family who wants the cutest dog to keep up with :)

Benny is 1.5 years old, 35lbs, microchipped and vaccinated. We are in the process of having him neutered.

Long story short... I'm from India! When I was three months old, I was found by locals laying in the middle of the road with my throat cut open. I don't really like to think about that anymore though, because ever since I was rescued, I've been living the life! The wonderful people in India took care of me until I was fully healed and ready to fly to New York. Can you believe it?! Me, a little puppy from India, traveling all the way around the world to find my perfect forever family in New York!

My foster mom in Hudson, New York says I'm a happy-go-lucky, very energetic and super sweet puppy with lots of love to give. I'm looking for an active family who is willing to train me and give me lots of exercise. Even though I'm still young, I'll always be high energy, so a big fenced-in yard and lots of walks/runs/hikes is what I'd love. I'm great with other dogs who also want to play all day long. I'm currently being fostered with three dogs and a cat. My foster family has worked on crate training me, which I'm doing well with, and I'm already housebroken. Another thing I love-- my family. I like to be around them all day, but because I'm high energy (but not aggressive), I'd do best with kids 10 years or older. I cannot wait to meet you!

My ideal family:
-A very active family who likes to go for walks/runs/hikes/to the dog park
-Big, fenced-in yard
-Another young dog in the house who likes to play a lot
-A family who is firm with training and willing to work with Benny
-A family member who works from home or is home a lot

Meet and greet/adoption will take place in Hudson, New York. If you are interested in adopting Benny, please fill out our application here: http://www.paws4survival.com/dog-application. Do not directly reply on petfinder. Post will be updated when Benny is adopted.

animal.description: This breathtaking five-year-old, male Siberian husky, “Happo,” weighs 64 pounds, loves treats, and can’t resist a belly rub. We believe he was an outside dog being used as a breed dog, before he was surrendered to the animal shelter. He bonded quickly with his handler, whose company he prefers over that of other dogs. He’s a little shy at first,  but loves the attention he is now getting. Happo can take a few minutes to warm up to strangers, but offering him a few treats speeds up his interest in new people. He still prefers to be outside, probably due to his super dense fluffy coat. He tolerates his crate and kennel but they are definitely not his favorite. He LOVES walks with his handler, which also fulfills the typical Husky need for exercise. Happo enjoys being mentally and physically stimulated, learning new tricks, and exploring new places. He is initially excited when on the leash, but once in a steady rhythm with his handler, he quickly matches stride. Hippo needs an experienced guardia, in a home without other animals/livestock, as he has a decent pray drive. He can live with other dogs, preferably submissive/passive females or young pups, and after more socialization we believe he’ll do well with most other dogs. Happo is a lovely fellow, who must find his FOREVER home. To get more information on a Pups On Parole dog, please contact a representative of the Lassen Humane Society at 530 251-7247 or e-mail ilovepopdogs@yahoo.com.  The Pups On Parole Program started in June of 2007 to help give homeless dogs a second chance at finding an adoptive family.  All dogs in the program spent time in our local county shelter, surrendered by their owners or picked up as strays and waiting for their owners to redeem them or to be adopted by new families.   The selected dogs are brought current on vaccinations, spayed/neutered if necessary, micro chipped, and heart worm tested.  They then are taken to the California Correctional Center Firehouse where they are assigned to a trainer/ inmate fire fighter.  These trainers groom and work with each dog and give them the extra time and attention they need to become wonderful family companions.   Most graduates are house trained and know basic obedience commands.  As of December 2018, 535 dogs have been adopted through this program.  To meet any of the Pups On Parole dogs, arrangements must be made in advance.

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Gilligan and I'm one of a family of Mom and 2 puppies, all of which were rescued from a busy street after we had been hit by a car.  I've been to a vet and have been all fixed up and I'm now ready to find my forever home.  I'm going to be a big, smart boy when I grow up. I'm still young, estimated DOB 11/9/2020 and probably have some Black Mouth Cur in my ancestry. I'm learning so much now that I'm in a home with other dogs and I love the whole family. I'm just a puppy and can get into a lot of trouble so you'll need to be willing to give me lots of gentle guidance, so I can learn all those big dog things, like how to behave in a house, what a crate is for, how to walk on a leash without pulling, and all those verbal commands every dog should know. I may even treat people like I treat my sibling with rough play or decide that new pair of shoes or a table leg would make a great chew toy, so a lot of appropriate toys should be in my future. The good news is that with the right training and LOTS of love, I'll be the best addition to your family ever and your best bud. If you are interested in me, please send an email to scpdogworld@gmail.com to get more information on how to fill out an application and have a great meet and greet to see if we are a match made in heaven.

animal.description:
Meet out sweet little muscle man Leo! 

We rescued Leo when he was “found” at a park and brought to our city’s shelter. He not only had swimmers syndrome he also has some pretty severe out turned hips & knees that make it difficult for him to get around. 
Leo needs daily physical therapy to keep his muscles loose and help him get around, he’s oh so cute but we really want people to try to look beyond that and understand this boy will probably always be special needs. 

He needs a non slippery surface in the home, his out turned hips and knees could be an orthopedic issue as he gets older so that needs to also be kept in mind and could be costly. 

He’s the sweetest guy that makes the funniest noises, he loves to play with playful dogs and snuggle with his favorite human. 

We are looking for a breed experienced home for him, and he is 7 months old!

Please visit our website and fill out an application to be considered. 
www.animalhelpalliance.org 

You will not be contacted if you don’t not 
1 Have an approved application on file. 
2 Don’t fill out an application.

animal.description:
Meet Missy, this adorable, senior girl is looking for her second home.  I would guess that Missy is a Chihuahua mix, of course, those ears !! But, she has a sturdy figure (weighs 17 lbs) , I would say resembles a dachshund, but not as long in length, with legs more on the Chi side (long).  Missy’s first home was so wonderful for 10 years, but her owner passed away and her veterinary promised her mom that she would make sure Missy was well taken care of and help find her a second home to live her golden years.  I am blessed to get to foster this lovely dog.  She is so sweet, low-maintenance, smart, loving, I could just go on and on with all of her greatness.  She is awesome with other dogs, great with cats.  Missy may be 10 years old, but she is fun, loves to run around backyard and play.  She loves her toys and of course, her treats.  She is house trained, leash trained, enjoys car rides. Missy has actually never had any flaws while being with me, she is easy going, and just fit right in my household.  She shares her food with others, no quarrels, no aggression.  Missy loves to cuddle, she also enjoys just lounging around in her dog bed as well taking life on day at time and enjoying every minute.  She has no health concerns at this time and her physical was great.  She has always been well-cared for and deserves to live her golden years as a spoiled companion.

If interested in adopting Missy, please complete our application at www.secondchanceresq.com

Our dogs are dogs are fostered in Texas but available for adoption in the Pacific Northwest (with stops in Seattle, WA; Portland; OR) through a partnership with Project Freedom Ride. The adoption application and fee would be finalized prior to transport. animal.description:
This is Rooney. He is an absolutely adorable freckle-faced 5-year-old, 47 lb. Aussie mix ready to bust out of the kennel. He was surrendered to us because he growled at the new baby in the home. 

Rooney reminds me of the movie "Grumpy Old Men" because all he does is growl. He growls when he's happy, he growls when he's sad. He growls to growl.  He loves to growl! I feel like there should be a poem in here somewhere.   Growling is his jam, but he's not aggressive! Kinda like me :) You MUST watch the video attached to truly understand.

He cat tested fine at the kennel, and he would be great as an only dog.  Any dogs in the home need to understand he will growl at them even when he's having fun and is playing. He also plays rough.  We are saying no kids because of his previous situation.  12 and up only, please.  Fenced yard not required if you commit to leash walking.

If you are interested in adopting this dog, please apply online, at https://bigfluffydogs.com/adopt/adoption-application/ then email Debbie@BigFluffyDogs.com.

Our main website, www.bigfluffydogs.com has more information about us and the rescue process. 

NOTE TO EMAILERS FROM PETFINDER: WE DO NOT RESPOND TO EMAIL INQUIRIES WITHOUT AN APPLICATION. WE REGRET WE CANNOT RESPOND TO EVERY EMAIL, BUT UNLESS YOU FILL OUT AN APPLICATION, WE DO NOT KNOW YOU EXIST. 

All known information about an individual dog is provided in its listing. We do our best to provide accurate information, but adopters should understand that each home is different and the dog may behave differently in a new home. Dogs are creatures of their environment and you help make the dog what it will be. Homes considering adopting a puppy must be prepared for 1.) Flexible schedules for potty training. Puppies can only hold it for one hour per month of age (i.e. a 4-month-old puppy can only go 4 hours without a potty break). 2.) Crate training until the puppy is at least one year old to prevent chewing on inappropriate things when you can't supervise. 3.) Socialization.  The more positive and varying experiences as a puppy the better, both in and out of your home. 4.) Puppy behavior and life stages are equivalent to a human toddler. It takes at least a full year to have a calmer, well-adjusted dog. Patience is required and when your dog's behavior is a positive experience for you and those around you, your patience will be rewarded ten-fold, for years to come.  Please do not consider adopting a puppy if you have not thoroughly thought through the pros and cons of having one. So many people end up returning them after 3-5 months because they didn't realize the amount of work involved in raising a puppy.  Patience, appropriate toys, socialization, and obedience training are all musts. All are time-consuming and can be expensive. All dogs require supervision with children and obedience training. Adopters that want to have good dogs must be prepared to put the time and effort into training a dog. Any dog requires work and effort, but a well trained, well-socialized dog is more than worth the effort to get them there.

animal.description:
Hi my name is Athena! I am approximately 2 years old. I came to SparKY after I was found with a broken back on the side of the road in April 2020. No one claimed me so SparKY stepped in to help me get better, I had a long recovery as my back took several months to mend. I am able to move my hind legs but unfortunately, I am no longer able to support my weight on them due to the nerve damage in my spine. I have a doggie wheelchair to help me walk when I go outside or in the house. I also have drag bags which I use inside so as I don’t get carpet burn on legs, my foster mom says I am the fastest two-legged dog you will meet. I am very much a beagle, I love to smell things when I am outside and will follow my nose if you allow me. I know the song of my people and have a very soulful beagle voice. I wear diapers as I leak urine a little. My foster mom will express my bladder so that I stay drier but it is not necessary for me to have it done as I can urinate when I go outside or if you hold me over a toilet or a pee pad. I love yard time outside with my fellow doggie housemates. I require a fenced in yard or someone to stay with me outside because I like to follow my nose wherever the smells take me. I will come with my cart, drag bags, and cloth diapers. I have a very soulful expression. I love to have my head patted and my neck rubbed. I am looking for my fur-ever home, will you please adopt me? I promise to be a good girl. 
Athena is up to date on vaccinations, heartworm negative, microchipped and spayed.  If you are interested in a Sparky pet , please go to www.sparkyrescue. com/adopting and fill out an application

animal.description:
Dusty is a gorgeous 3-4 month old terrier mix puppy. He’s playful, loving and so very sweet. Dusty is about 15 lbs currently and expected to be in the large size range when full grown. He’s good with other dogs and cats. He LOVES kids and truly brightens up when one comes around. Dusty is a very active boy and would do best in an active home. He’s working on house and kennel training as well as his puppy manners. 

Please note: as with most rescue puppies, we have no way to guarantee this puppy’s breed or size potential. 

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information. 

2021 Adoption Fee Scale for non-benefactor animals:
Puppies under 12 months - $300
Dogs over 12 months - $200

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

*Any breed labels used by Take Paws Rescue, its employees/volunteers, or on vet records provided cannot be guaranteed.  Breed labels are given based on information obtained during intake and/or best guesses based on appearance and/or temperament of the dogs and Take Paws Rescue gives no assurance to the accuracy of these labels. Labels are necessary for postings to many animal networking sites, such as Pet Finder, and are no way a guarantee. Additionally, exact age and potential size cannot be guaranteed.
